| law_reject_window | 9.959 | 3.125 | 3.1869 | 64 | one REFUSED 9th-attempt commit on the saturated task 0 per sample (Cardinality cited) |
| law_reject_scope | 7.417 | 2.791 | 2.6575 | 64 | one REFUSED Observe-steer scope commit per sample (the ψ containment cited) |

## lane `nosync`

Db::ephemeral (MDB_NOSYNC: pages and meta pwritten, no sync boundary ever crossed) vs SQLite WAL synchronous=OFF fullfsync=OFF checkpoint_fullfsync=OFF, cache_size=-262144, temp_store=MEMORY, whole-file mmap (coverage asserted), wal_autocheckpoint=0 — WAL frames written, never synced (OFF, not NORMAL: NORMAL still syncs at checkpoints, which would cross-match a store kind that never syncs)

| family | ours p50 µs | sqlite p50 µs | ratio p50 (ours/sqlite) | work | about |
|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---|
| law_commit_attempt | 23.500 | 22.333 | 1.0523 | 64 | one judged Attempt insert per commit under the full law roster (key + containment + window) |
| law_commit_cluster | 48.542 | 54.167 | 0.8962 | 256 | one judged 4-row cluster per commit: attempt + verdict + steer + scope — every statement family exercised in one commit |
| law_reject_key | 15.125 | 3.333 | 4.5380 | 64 | one REFUSED duplicate-(task, n) commit per sample (Functionality cited) |
| law_reject_containment | 9.083 | 5.584 | 1.6266 | 64 | one REFUSED absent-task commit per sample (Containment cited) |
| law_reject_window | 9.625 | 3.125 | 3.0800 | 64 | one REFUSED 9th-attempt commit on the saturated task 0 per sample (Cardinality cited) |
| law_reject_scope | 7.292 | 2.791 | 2.6127 | 64 | one REFUSED Observe-steer scope commit per sample (the ψ containment cited) |

### rejection latency

The `law_reject_*` rows price a REFUSED commit round-trip: on the engine, the full dependency judgment plus the abort (`Error::CommitRejected`, the complete violation set decoded); on SQLite, the constraint failure — UNIQUE, FK, or a trigger's `RAISE(ABORT)` — plus the `ROLLBACK`. No rejected sample commits anything on either engine (the post-state fold certifies it).
